ce:section.ce:para:
As for the design and synthesis of CDs, a plethora of small molecules, polymers, and biomass have been screened as raw materials, such as citric acid [17], phenylenediamine (PD) [17,18], naphthalene [25], polythiophene [26], amino acids [27], and carbohydrates [28]. Epigallocatechin gallate (EGCG) that comes from green natural plant polyphenol can mitigate amyloid formation and cytotoxicity [29]. The catechol structure of EGCG endows it with metal chelating, anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and neuroprotective activities, which play critical roles in treating AD [6,30]. Therefore, this work was designed to develop potent CDs by using EGCG as one of the raw materials, which would empower the synthesized CDs with elevated inhibitory efficacy and other functionalities that are very different from currently available CDs [16,18,31,32]. Furthermore, it was demonstrated that the fluorescent characteristics of CDs could be modulated by doping heteroatom-containing additives such as o-phenylenediamine (oPD) [16,17,33]. Thus, to fabricate fluorescent EGCG-derived carbonized polymer dots (E-CPDs), EGCG and oPD were selected as the carbon and nitrogen sources, respectively. By controlling the reaction conditions during the hydrothermal process, the functional residues of EGCG would be retained, and the fluorescent properties of E-CPDs might be regulated. Importantly, the inhibitory efficiency of E-CPDs could be further enhanced due to the introduction of positively charged oPD, which may enhance the electrostatic interactions between CDs and Aβ species [18]. Through a series of in vitro and in vivo experiments, the multifunctionality of E-CPDs on inhibition of Aβ fibrils formation, rapid disaggregation of mature Aβ fibrils, reactive oxygen species (ROS) scavenging, and fluorescent detection of Aβ plaques was systematically investigated (Scheme 1
                     a
                     ). This is a proof-of-concept research on the synthesis of multifunctional polyphenol-derived CDs for scavenging Aβ plaques, and it is possible to inspire a new direction for AD theranostics by multifunctional CDs.
